<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<h2 id="apprenticeships-that-start-before-1-august-2021">Apprenticeships that start before 1 August 2021</h2>

<p>UK nationals living in the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/eu-eea" class="govuk-link"><abbr title="The European Economic Area - it includes EU countries and also Iceland, Liechtenstein and Norway">EEA</abbr> or Switzerland</a> wishing to start an apprenticeship in England before 1 August 2021 will continue to be eligible on the same basis as now.</p>

<p>Find out more about <a href="https://www.gov.uk/apprenticeships-guide" class="govuk-link">becoming an apprentice</a>.</p>

<h2 id="apprenticeships-starting-from-1-august-2021">Apprenticeships starting from 1 August 2021</h2>

<p>You will continue to be eligible for an apprenticeship in England if you meet the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/apprenticeship-funding-rules" class="govuk-link">eligibility requirements</a> in place at the time, including that:</p>

<ul>
  <li>you are living in the <abbr title="The European Economic Area - it includes EU countries and also Iceland, Liechtenstein and Norway">EEA</abbr> or Switzerland on 31 December 2020</li>
  <li>you have been living in the <abbr title="The European Economic Area - it includes EU countries and also Iceland, Liechtenstein and Norway">EEA</abbr>, Switzerland, the UK or Gibraltar for at least the last 3 years before starting an apprenticeship</li>
  <li>you have lived continuously in the <abbr title="The European Economic Area - it includes EU countries and also Iceland, Liechtenstein and Norway">EEA</abbr>, Switzerland, the UK or Gibraltar between 31 December 2020 and the start of your apprenticeship</li>
  <li>you will spend at least 50% of your working hours in England during your apprenticeship</li>
  <li>the apprenticeship starts before 1 January 2028</li>
</ul>

<p>Your children will also be eligible for an apprenticeship in England on the same terms even if they are not themselves UK nationals.</p>

<h2 id="apprenticeships-outside-england">Apprenticeships outside England</h2>

<p>For information on apprenticeships in Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland, visit the websites for each country:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a rel="external" href="https://www.apprenticeships.scot/" class="govuk-link">Scotland</a></li>
  <li><a rel="external" href="https://businesswales.gov.wales/skillsgateway/skills-and-training-programmes/apprenticeships" class="govuk-link">Wales</a></li>
  <li>
    <p><a rel="external" href="https://www.nidirect.gov.uk/campaigns/apprenticeships" class="govuk-link">Northern Ireland</a></p>

  </li>
</ul>
</div>
